By: Bruce Norman
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The munchkin is a character class designed for those that want to do
*everything*.  Actually, its possible to make a character class more powerful
than the munchkin, but why bother?

The Munchkin
A new character class (designed using the DMG rules on page 22)

- Can be of any race
- Attacks as monster of same level
- Saves as Warrior of same level
- d12 hit points per level
- Can wear all armor
- Can learn any weapon
- +3hp per level beyond 9th
- Gains fighter constitution bonuses, and may roll for exceptional strength
- Eight weapon proficiences at first level
- Aura of Protection vs Evil (or good, dep on alignment) as Paladin
- Backstabs as thief of same level
- Casts Priest spells as priest of same level (all spheres)
- Casts Mage spells as mage of same level (all schools)
- Can use magical items availible to fighters, clerics, mages and thieves.

XP modifier: 44

Level 2:    8,800
      3:   17,600
      4:   35,200
      5:   88,000
      6:  176,000
      7:  352,000
      8:  660,000
      9: 1,232,000
    10+: 1,320,000 per level

 * Origin: WNN = Satan's Dentist! (FidoNet 1:249/106.5)
